

	 
      We try to raise our kids to just walk away. Stanton was raised that way and sometimes when we have had a enough we fight back. I think anyone would feel good about fighting back when they had no choice.However that goodfeeling is temporary.   We are taught not to fight back, yet there is a certain satisfaction in retaliating. Then our hearts take over and we know hurting someone only hurts us.     
     
    
